The paper discusses the use of federated learning, a machine learning technique, to improve data privacy and security in mobile networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses on optimizing federated learning algorithms and designing incentive mechanisms, the most likely category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, and cs.AI.
